---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="For Families" description="Understanding trauma therapy - a guide for parents and caregivers supporting their child's treatment.">
  <section class="py-10 sm:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12">
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl font-semibold text-charcoal mb-4">
          For Families
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed">
          Your child has started trauma therapy, and you want to understand what's happening and how you can help. You're in the right place.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Reassurance Section -->
      <div class="bg-forest-50 rounded-lg p-8 mb-12 max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-charcoal mb-4">
          You're Not Alone
        </h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          It's natural to have questions and concerns about your child's therapy. Learning about the treatment process can help you feel more confident and better equipped to support your child's healing journey.
        </p>
        <p class="text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed">
          The guides on this site are written in plain language by trauma therapists who work with families every day. We explain what happens in therapy without overwhelming jargon.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Treatment Guides -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-charcoal mb-6">
          Understanding Your Child's Treatment
        </h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <Card href="/families/emdr" title="What is EMDR?" variant="featured">
            <p class="text-charcoal/80 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
              EMDR (Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing) helps the brain process traumatic memories. Learn what your child experiences and how you can support them.
            </p>
            <span class="inline-block text-xs font-medium px-2 py-1 bg-forest-100 text-forest-700 rounded">
              Available Now
            </span>
          </Card>

          <Card title="What is TF-CBT?">
            <p class="text-charcoal/80 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Trauma-Focused Cognitive Behavioral Therapy helps children and teens process trauma through structured activities.
            </p>
            <span class="inline-block text-xs font-medium px-2 py-1 bg-wood-200 text-wood-700 rounded">
              Coming Soon
            </span>
          </Card>

          <Card title="What is PCIT?">
            <p class="text-charcoal/80 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Parent-Child Interaction Therapy strengthens the parent-child bond and teaches effective parenting skills.
            </p>
            <span class="inline-block text-xs font-medium px-2 py-1 bg-wood-200 text-wood-700 rounded">
              Coming Soon
            </span>
          </Card>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What to Expect Section -->
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-charcoal mb-6">
          What to Expect
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-charcoal/80">
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-forest-100 text-forest-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold text-sm">
              1
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-charcoal mb-1">Building Trust</h3>
              <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
                The first sessions focus on helping your child feel safe with their therapist. The therapist will explain what therapy will be like and answer your questions.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-forest-100 text-forest-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold text-sm">
              2
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-charcoal mb-1">Learning Coping Skills</h3>
              <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
                Before processing trauma, your child will learn techniques to manage stress and feel safe. These are skills they can use anywhere.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-forest-100 text-forest-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold text-sm">
              3
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-charcoal mb-1">Processing Memories</h3>
              <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
                When ready, your child will work through difficult memories in a safe, controlled way. This helps the brain heal from trauma.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-forest-100 text-forest-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-semibold text-sm">
              4
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-charcoal mb-1">Healing and Growth</h3>
              <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
                As therapy progresses, your child will develop new, healthier ways of thinking about themselves and their experiences.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Support Tips -->
      <div class="mt-12 p-6 border border-wood-200 rounded-lg max-w-3xl">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-charcoal mb-4">
          How You Can Help
        </h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-charcoal/80">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-forest-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
            Be patient — healing takes time and isn't always linear
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-forest-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
            Keep communication open without pushing
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-forest-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
            Maintain routines and stability at home
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-forest-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
            Ask the therapist how to support specific skills at home
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-forest-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
            Take care of yourself too — your wellbeing matters
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
